I’m not a biologist or a conspiracy theorist but something is going on recently with 9 dead whales washing up on the shores of NJ and NY in the last few months. Sad to see these majestic animals lives ended too soon. This one was only a short drive from where I live. My fellow downeast Mainers getting choked out of the lobster fishing business with restrictions and red listing aimed at “protecting “ right whales yet studies show a right whale has not been killed in over 20 years from lobster fishing off the Maine coast do to already strict regulations. Really makes you question who’s best interest politicians have in mind. I see no real investigation into these whale deaths here and the suspicion that it’s related to off shore windmills yet they are more that willing to end many generations of fishing for lobster men and women along the coast of Maine with a complete blind eye to real facts and statistics. Sad . Politicians once again failing us. Support Maine Lobster fisherman. If you’ve ever been to the rocky shores of the Maine coast it’s pristine for a reason. They care about the ocean and the creatures who live in it. #DowneastMainer

I was humbled today by the spirit and the love of my community for a little boy named Jaxon who has a dream one day of becoming a police officer . Jaxon has something called Neurofibromatosis or NF1 for short. His mother @stacifuge and father @dfuge1982 started a campaign for him called #PatchesForJax . You can read more about it and how to get involved by following @stacifuge .  The amount of mail and PD patches this little boy has received is absolutely incredible and the campaign continues for any Leo’s who are seeing this or those who may have a Leo family member . Todays event  for Jaxon was sponsored and organized by Bradley Beach Police Dept . Specifically officer Billy Major. The turn out from countless Monmouth county police departments as well as @njstatepolice_  and fire departments was something that just makes you proud to be part of this community. Thank you to all who showed up to support Jaxon and his family. Good still exists in this crazy world and I think we all saw the pure exhilaration in Jaxon’s eyes today. I’m not sure he was even able to take it all in but I’m sure mom and dad got lots of pictures and videos to show him when they get home . Special thanks to @realshoregood food truck for donating their time, truck and food to all the amazing people who came out today to show support .  Good wins in the end. Believe.

My dad @bill_mathews248 who I love dearly is not the most tech savvy fella you ever met sent me this “memory” that just appeared in his phone and he didn’t know how it got there. I explained to him Apple phones create music slideshows on their own but you can turn it off if you want in settings. It was created because a few years ago Meilani had to do a school project on her family tree on both sides and needed some pics so my dad sent me these. Pretty cool rewatching them (other than the music apple picked to go along with it )now. The first pic is my Dad and the last pic is my grandmother, Grammy Mathews. I only ever remember her with white as snow hair. She was the best lady I ever knew. Always made me food no matter what time of day or night I showed up. She made the best homemade biscuits on planet earth.  Loved me unconditionally and I could do no wrong in her eyes. There were times when I was a teenager and my dad wanted to kill me (rightly so as I was a hell raising asshat) that lady would  stick up for me and tell her own son, my father to “Calm down, he’s a good kid Bill !”What was he gonna say ? That was his mother. I miss you Gram. Had some dark days where I needed you but I still talked to you like you were right there next to me . We got through. #DowneastMainer

Sometimes the coyotes are so close he can almost see their eyes shining from the fire. The man don’t fear much cause he has god by his side. Blessed to call him my Dad.

Lots of people struggle to pronounce Meilani’s name correctly and many ask how she came to be called Meilani. (Trust me I am MOST DEFINITELY not one of those people who get offended if you mispronounce her name ) Many of you are familiar with @bethanyhamilton but many people don’t know her middle name is Meilani. In Hawaiian it means heavenly flower. So she’s not named per say after Bethany but a chance meeting with Bethany certainly was the inspiration behind naming our daughter Meilani. How could you not love the meaning behind the name for a first born and beautiful little girl and how could you not love Bethany and her inspirational story and person. #HeavenlyFlower
